#Id And Classes
✅ Class Selector (.)
Used for grouping multiple elements.

Starts with a dot (.) in CSS.

Can be reused on multiple elements.
<p class="highlight">This is highlighted text.</p>
<div class="highlight">This is also highlighted.</div>
.highlight {
  background-color: yellow;
  font-weight: bold;
}
✅ ID Selector (#)
Used to target a single unique element.

Starts with a hash (#) in CSS.

Should not be reused on multiple elements (each ID must be unique).
<h1 id="main-title">Welcome</h1>
#main-title {
  color: blue;
  font-size: 36px;
}
